com.amazon.insights
Class InsightsCallback<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.amazon.insights.InsightsCallback<T>

public abstract class InsightsCallback<T>
extends java.lang.Object

The InsightsCallback is the callback object that you can set on an InsightsHandler via InsightsHandler.setCallback(InsightsCallback) to react upon success or failure of the associated asynchronous method. On success, the handler's return object is passed into the onComplete method as an argument; but on failure, an InsightsError reference is passed into the onError method which indicates the reason for the error.

onError

public void onError(InsightsError error)
When the InsightsHandler object this callback has been registered with fails, it calls onError with an InsightsError object that contains detailed information regarding the error. The base implementation will log the error into a human-readable format to the Android log; if you want custom handling, you must override this method. By doing so, you may prevent the logging of the error from occurring unless you call super.onError(error).

Parameters:
error - an InsightsError object that provides detailed information regarding the error
